<dl id="n16016f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16016f">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16016f"> 16(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ amulet <font face="wake">C</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It could be, and was, urged at the time that as the carrying of these curious objects <font color="green">[alleged anti-gas masks]</font> seemed to calm the civilian population in a moment of national emergency, they served a useful purpose. The same argument has been brought forward on behalf of <mark>amulets</mark> and other pious frauds sold in the name of religion. <small> J.B.S. Haldane, <a name="CHEM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHEM"><cite title="source">Callinicus</cite></a> (1925) 33</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c02138f" href="c02all.htm#c02138f">VI.C.02:138(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
